	   <a name=96707812525284></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96707812525284><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=96707812525284>Root & DOT</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=96707812525284#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=959><span id= >Booz</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>4 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Aug 23rd 8:48 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.33]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>This is the most efficient method for a shaman to solo at levels 24+.&nbsp;&nbsp;DOTs are the most mana efficient damage spells the shaman gets, and by rooting the mob you ensure that they take full damage from the DOT.  You can also slow the mob and haste yourself and melee the mob while doted and root if you get hurt to much.  Do this to keep your offence, defence and melee skills maxed for your level.  Since there is a message when your DOT wears off, just reapply it and re apply root, and you can sit and meditate or do the shaman dance (meditate and canibalize) while your DOT kills the mob.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>
<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=96743152228510></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96743152228510><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=96743152228510>RE: Root & DOT</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=96743152228510#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=492><span id=Sage>Gorthin</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>149 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Aug 27th 10:58 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Just a quick warning with the "Shaman Dance of Death" aka Med/cannabilize.&nbsp;&nbsp;If it is a close fight (solo at least), avoid the temptation to cannabilize down really low to get that extra little mana to get another spell off unless you are completely sure the fight is in the bag.  Mobs have a tendency to frenzy on you when you least expect it.  There is nothing worse than seeing a mob turn to run, you canning to get enough mana to nuke it down (most often in an area where others assist it), and suddenly the monster deciding since you are low on hp to frenzy on you.<br>I canned down to about half a bubb at a zone line to finish off a MOB the other day when it ran (all my DoT's had worn off and I was very LOM) when suddenly it turned, double hit me for a total of 120 damage, and knocked me out.  Regen started to do its thing while it missed me, but then it got in one shot right before I went conscious again.  Heh, lesson learned the hard way =)<br>Gorthin 37 Shaman who hasn't been playing since the wife is on Vacation<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
