	   <tr><td colspan=2>this is my experiance as a barbarian shaman on brell serelis.<br><br>levels 1 - 7 can be soloed in everfrost. at level 5 start killing gnolls outside BB, and save polar bear pelts ( the white ones ) and sell them to people in everfrost doing polar bear cloak quest, or give it to the female merchant in macs kilts at halas for raw-hide armor and exp. from 7 - 9, group in black burrow, by now you should be useing a craked staff. at level 9 you get sow, possibly the most usefull spell in the game, which you can sell to people around the area and make good cash, at this time you should eithor get a bloodforge hammer for around 10p, or if youre rich, you can get a cold iron morning star from some high level farmers in permafrost for around 30-50p. at this time, go to wisp isle ( eruds crossing ). to get there take the boat from south qeynos. kill the wisps and snakes, they are great loot and exp. you can take the greaters lightstone to gypsies in north karana for exelent exp, and they give you a book that sells for 8p, or if youre lazy you can sell the greater lightstones for 7p. here you can get real rich, save for banded armor and a 1 handed magic weapon if you dont have alredy, aslo get jasper earings and rings. at around 15 solo in tundra till 16. at 16, you can go to highpass hold for great loot and exp, or solo the oasis for great exp, no loot though =(. if you are luckey enough to win stuff in highpass, go for&nbsp;&nbsp;a charred gaurdian sheild, 10ac 9wis. at this time i was useing an enameld black mace, 8/28 magic, and a CGS. stay at highpass till 19 then go back to halas to buy spells and souch. thats the end of part 1 for me.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>&#8224;°&#8226;=THORG FROSTFIST=&#8226;°&#8224;<br>60th season shaman<br>Brell Serilis<br>**Retired**</td></tr>
