	   <tr><td colspan=2>It is true I'm afraid anonymous.<br>When you hit lvl 29 you get greater healing.&nbsp;&nbsp;Now you are just as good as a cleric, but with more hitpoints and can help in combat when you are full on mana.<br><br>You will remain a primary healer until about 39 (whenever clerics get superior healing).  At that time you are exactly this in a group:<br>Buffer, Debuffer, DoT'er, and chloro.<br><br>Reason we are not healers after lvl 39:<br>1) we can just blast the mob to death and be more efficient than our greater healing spell.<br>2) mobs hit for about double 90s at that level.  Two of these and your greater heal spell is already gone.<br>3) Your slow line of spells is better than ANY heal spell in your book in terms of keeping health.<br><br>You need to try to figure out what verant intending by making x-spell.  Every spell verant created revolves around grouping and roleplaying.  Its up to you from there.<br><br>Good luck sir!<br>&nbsp;<br>Grimlach Blackhand - Prophet, Innoruuk server.</td></tr>
