	   <tr><td colspan=2>Nice post there, but i must say that in my opinion, i dont see how fun can playing a shaman solely as a healer can be... By that i just try to express the boredomness of not playing a character to its full extent. Im aware of the group situations and i agree that if you are the only healer type in a group, well you have to heal. But groups after 50+ cant be well balanced without a cleric as of my experience shows... But again its just me :) <br><br>Heres a funny story that explains why im posting this : The other night i was in Karnor ( doing skelly warlord ) then the monk ( 30 secs after i have joined the group in the middle of a fight and worked my mojo ) starts to explain to me how to play my class... He said : slow, sit and heal you cant melee and you cant take damage, let the big guys handle the fights. I replied well i appreciate your comment but let me play 1 hour as i always do and get back to me later, afterall we had a cleric and a bard. <br><br>Then i started my mojo :)<br><br>&lt;Made a pet... buffed all melee including me and Fluffy(tm) then cannibalized some mana while fighting some respawns. i have not sit a fight in the whole hour, medding in pull time, cannibalizing between casts of JBB in fighting, slowing,&nbsp;&nbsp;dotting  and wacking a bit with my big bad Barb Spiritist`s hammer, while the dog was chewing up some mobs. <br><br>After the hour, seeing i was always 50% mana and up kept backing up on heals and was doing some nice damage, the monk said well i must admit u play yur shaman in a diffrent way then most of yer brothers, i think ill make a shaman soon :P i tought shamans were only debufferss/healers<br><br>On a final note, im level 54 and the monk was level 51... he had 860AC god he was pissed hearing i had 908 AC buffed :P<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
